Mozambique is regularly affected by natural disasters, including floods, drought and cyclones.
Tropical Storm Eloise is expected to strengthen to a Tropical Cyclone, bringing hazardous sea and weather conditions to Central and Southern Mozambique from Friday 22 January 2020. It is expected to affect Zambezia, Sofala, Inhambane, Gaza and Maputo Provinces. There is a risk of flooding in affected areas. Follow the advice of the local authorities, which includes advice to stay at home from 3pm on 22 January in Sofala and Zambezia provinces. Monitor local reports and international weather updates from the World Meteorological Organisation, check your routes before travelling around the country.
